# TEC.ERP Engineering

Consult `.cursor/context/TEC_ERP_PROJECT_CONTEXT.md` and `docs/19_CURSOR_MASTER_BUILD_SPECIFICATION.md` before implementing.

## Vertical Delivery

Each feature is a complete vertical slice (`docs/19` §6–7):

Architecture → Backend → Frontend → Simulation → Testing → Documentation → Validation → Production Readiness

Incomplete slices must not be merged.

## Definition of Complete

A feature is done only when functionality, business rules, UI, API docs, tests, documentation, and deployment validation all pass (`docs/19` §7).

## Approval Gate (mandatory)

Before commit or next phase, validate (`docs/19` §9):

Business Rules · UI · Backend · Simulation · Database · API · Testing · Documentation · Production Readiness

If any item fails, the phase stays open. Never continue after a failed gate (BUILD-005).

## Stack Constraints

- **TypeScript** strict mode — no `any`, explicit interfaces (`docs/19` §36)
- **React** functional, small, composable components (`docs/19` §37)
- **Express** business-oriented REST endpoints (`docs/18` §2)
- **Prisma + PostgreSQL** — versioned, tested migrations (`docs/19` §79, `docs/17`)
- **Railway** — all decisions must remain deployable (`docs/19` §77.1, `docs/25`)

## Quality & Testing

- Business and educational value before technical complexity (ENG-007, `docs/22` §4)
- EduQA: verify mission quality and learning outcomes (`docs/22` §24)
- Risk-based testing with evidence for release (`docs/23` §3–4)
- Security-by-design on every change (`docs/26` §3)

## BUILD Rules

BUILD-001 Never skip documentation · BUILD-002 Never implement without architecture · BUILD-003 Never merge failing tests · BUILD-004 Never duplicate business rules · BUILD-005 Never continue after failed gate · BUILD-006 Always leave repo buildable (`docs/19` §15)

## Structural Changes

Before architectural changes, evaluate impact per `docs/19` §95: Business → Educational → Database → API → Frontend → Simulation → Testing → Deployment → Documentation.
